\title{scalar matrix}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-05-12}
\import{ela}

\p{A diagonal matrix #{\mat{A}=(a_{i,j})} for which #{a_{i,i}=c} for all #{i} is called a \define{Scalar Matrix}.}

\p{The word "scalar" intuitively means "number". We [motivated](ela-0009) matrices by trying to generalize numbers. Scalar matrices are "the most number-like" among matrices.}